**Set Up Git Repository on Storage Server**

The Nautilus development team has provided requirements to the DevOps team for a new application development project, specifically requesting the establishment of a Git repository. Follow the instructions below to create the Git repository on the Storage server in the Stratos DC:

1. Utilize yum to install the git package on the Storage Server.

2. Create a bare repository named /opt/apps.git (ensure exact name usage).

**Solution**

Step1: Login to storage server.
Step2: Do cat /etc/*release to find the OS release.
Step3: sudo yum install git -y.
Step4: run git --version to check whether git is installed.
Step5: sudo git init --bare /opt/official.git 

To create a bare Git repository from scratch, navigate to your desired directory in your terminal and run the command git init --bare repository_name.git. A bare repository contains only the Git version control history database and does not include a working directory to edit project files directly, making it ideal to act as a centralized remote server or a shared hub for collaboration.